OL,3,CProgramme listings for
OL,3,CProgramme listings for SUN 17 MAY
OL,4,G1900FNature: The Classical Collection
OL,5,     GThe natural world has always been
OL,6,     Ga powerful inspiration to
OL,7,     Gcomposers, and this programme
OL,8,     Gtakes us on an evocative journey
OL,9,     Gthrough some of the best-loved
OL,10,     Gmusical responses.
OL,11,G1915FA Wild Year
OL,12,     GIn the north east of England lies
OL,13,     Ga wild and remote moorland. This
OL,14,     Gancient landscape of heather-clad
OL,15,     Guplands and sheltered dales is
OL,16,     Ghome to red grouse and tough
OL,17,     Gmoorland sheep.
OL,18,G2015FRomeo and Juliet with Rudolf
OL,19,     FNureyev and Margot Fonteyn
OL,20,     GMargot Fonteyn and Rudolf Nureyev
OL,21,     Gstar in the Royal Ballet's Romeo
OL,22,     Gand Juliet. From 1977.
OL,23,Vppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
